    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Carrying devices or frames carried across a person's shoulders that consist of a length of material, usually wood, sometimes shaped to accommodate the neck and shoulders of the user, though this is often a simple rod. Suspended from this support are two buckets that can transport liquid or other materials by one person.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
